	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Cape Town – A 16-year-old boy has been stabbed to death in Paarl East, Western Cape police confirmed on Sunday. The teenager was killed in Jan Fiskaal Street in the suburb of Amstelhofat around 18:30 on Saturday, said spokesperson, Captain FC van Wyk. It was not immediately clear what had happened. Van Wyk said police were investigating the murder and no arrests had yet been made.    24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.